subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
This species belongs to the 

phyllicola

group according to 

Deeleman-Reinhold (
2001
)

. It resembles 

U. phyllicola

Deeleman-Reinhold, 
2001


by the male palpal genital bulb being as long as wide, the embolus coils are much narrower than the genital bulb, the female vulval bursae are far from the spermathecae but close to the pedicel; however, it can be distinguished from 

U. phyllicola

by: 
1
) the tegulum being obviously smaller than that of the latter; 
2
) having the subtegulum visible in ventral view, whereas it is not visible in 

U. phyllicola

; 
3
) having much narrower embolus coils than the latter; 
4
) having an atrium that is wider than long, whereas it is longer than wide in 

U. phyllicola

; 
5
) ovoid bursae, whereas they are not ovoid in the latter; 
6
) copulatory ducts that are longitudinal and nearly straight, whereas they are transverse and helical in 

U. phyllicola

.
